Johannesburg - A 21-year-old man was arrested , in the Johannesburg CBD for attempted murder, police said on Tuesday. &nbsp; Police spokesperson Captain Xoli Mbele, stationed at Johannesburg Central, said on New Year's Eve the suspect allegedly assaulted a 32-year-old male with pavement bricks at the corner of Anderson and Alexander Streets.&nbsp; &quot;The suspect confronted the victim who was walking passing underneath a bridge, he started assaulting him with bricks until he was unconscious and robbed him his cell phone,&quot; said Mbele.&nbsp; Community members made a citizen's arrest and called the police. The victim was taken by ambulance to hospital.&nbsp; The suspect will appear in the Johannesburg Magistrate's Court soon.&nbsp; African News Agency